The Chronicle Chronicle Reporter THE country recorded 610 new Covid-19 positive cases and 13 deaths in the last 24 hours. The seven-day rolling for new cases further spiked to 597 from 552 yesterday. <img class="alignnone wp-image-491018 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/covid191.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/covid191.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/covid191-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> All of the 610 positive cases are local transmission. A total of 4 696 PCR tests were conducted. New recoveries were 153. <img class="alignnone wp-image-493293 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/corona-1.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="379" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/corona-1.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/corona-1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The national recovery rate stands at 67percent and active cases went up to 5047. “As of 6 January, 2020, Zimbabwe has now recorded 17804 cases, 11966 recoveries and 431 deaths,” reads statistics from the Ministry of Health and Child Care.